Package: SpiderMonkey
Title: Embeds the JavaScript interpreter Spider Monkey within R
Version: 0.2-0
Author: Duncan Temple Lang
Maintainer: Duncan Temple Lang <duncan@r-project.org>
License: MPL-2.0
Depends: RAutoGenRunTime, bitops
Imports: Rffi
Description:  This package provides a mechanism for
  R to execute JavaScript, create JavaScript objects and
  call JavaScript methods. This can be used  by embedding
  the JavaScript engine in R or alternatively embedding
  R within the a mozilla application, e.g. Firefox browser 
  or Thunderbird and accessing the JavaScript  engine
  "from within".

